From the mouth of the Don to the Canopic mouth of the Nile the most careful authorities have made the distance 2110 miles. Artemidorus thought that the regions beyond had not been explored, though admitting that the tribes of the Sarmatae dwell round the Don to the north- ward. Isidorus added 1350 miles right on to Thule, which is a purely conjectural estimate. I under- stand that the territory of the Sarmatae is known to an extent not less than the limit just stated. And from another aspect, how large is the space bound to be that is large enough to hold innumerable races that are continually migr-ating? This makes me think that there is an uninhabitable region beyond of much wider extent ; for I am informed that beyond Germany also there are vast islands that were dis- covered not long ago.
